Plot as a scatterplot


penguins |&gt; 
  group_by(year, species) |&gt; 
  summarise(count = n()) |&gt; 
  ggplot(
    aes(x = year, 
        y = count)
  ) +
  geom_point()

Adding another layer


penguins |&gt; 
  group_by(year, species) |&gt; 
  summarise(count = n()) |&gt; 
  ggplot(
    aes(x = year, 
        y = count)
  ) +
  geom_point() + 
  geom_line()

Adding group


penguins |&gt; 
  group_by(year, species) |&gt; 
  summarise(count = n()) |&gt; 
  ggplot(
    aes(x = year, 
        y = count,
        group = species)
  ) +
  geom_point() + 
  geom_line()

Layering geoms


penguins |&gt; 
  group_by(year, species) |&gt; 
  summarise(count = n()) |&gt; 
  ggplot(
    aes(x = year, 
        y = count,
        group = species,
        label = count)
  ) +
  geom_point() + 
  geom_line() + 
  geom_text()

Layering geoms


penguins |&gt; 
  group_by(year, species) |&gt; 
  summarise(count = n()) |&gt; 
  ggplot(
    aes(x = year, 
        y = count,
        group = species,
        label = count)
  ) +
  geom_point() + 
  geom_line() + 
  geom_text(nudge_y = 2)

Global mapping Vs local mapping


penguins |&gt; 
  group_by(year, species) |&gt; 
  summarise(count = n()) |&gt; 
  ggplot(
    aes(x = year, 
        y = count,
        group = species,
        label = count)
  ) +
  geom_point() + 
  geom_line(
    aes(color = species)
  ) + 
  geom_text(nudge_y = 2)

Geom-specific properties


penguins |&gt; 
  group_by(year, species) |&gt; 
  summarise(count = n()) |&gt; 
  ggplot(
    aes(x = year, 
        y = count,
        group = species,
        label = count)
  ) +
  geom_point(
    size = 3
  ) + 
  geom_line(
    aes(color = species)
  ) + 
  geom_text(
    nudge_y = 2,
    color = "grey40")

